## B3d Phase-A audit (2026-06-26) — HEALTHY-with-fixes, no push (audit committed c93bade)

Audited 90aa8d5..c9c8e30 (B3d-4/5z/5). All three integrity gates ENFORCED +
unbypassable on the production path (OCI blob sha256 digest, zip CRC-32+size,
cue.sum h1). Inflate total + robust. No Violation, no security hole. Two
fix-slices filed in plan.md (§ "B3d Phase-A audit"):

- **B3d-A1 (soundness, MED, top-ranked):** writeModuleToCache extracts entries
  non-atomically and locateModuleDir trusts the extract dir on bare pathExists —
  a crash MID-EXTRACT leaves a partial module a later run loads silently (wrong
  value, no re-fetch). NOT a security bypass (bytes are digest+CRC verified
  before write; a tamper can't pass), crash-windowed. Filed as a slice, NOT
  fixed inline (touches the live IO write path + needs a same-fs temp dir for
  the atomic rename — beyond the low-risk-inline bar). What you'd do: approve
  the extract-to-temp + IO.FS.rename slice (the proper fix), or say "inline it"
  to take it now.
- **B3d-A2 (test-strength, LOW):** adversarial DEFLATE/ZIP reject branches
  under-pinned (only BTYPE=3). Add error-marker native_decide pins. Slice.

No inline fixes this audit. lake build clean (130 jobs); check-fixtures.sh
green; shellcheck clean. Committed c93bade (plan.md only) — NOT pushed (AFK).

